# Security Standards

## Authentication & Authorization

- Every API route must call `supabase.auth.getUser()` and reject if no user.
- Check resource-level permissions with `checkBucketAccess()` before operations.
- RLS policies enforce access at DB level; client code provides defense-in-depth.

## Input Validation

- Validate all user input (required fields, types, lengths, formats).
- Validate UUID format with regex before passing to queries.
- Sanitize HTML input with `DOMPurify` before storage.

## Secrets & Environment

- **Never expose** secrets with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix.
- Server-only secrets: `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET`
- Safe to expose: `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY`
- Validate required env vars on startup with `validateEnv()`.

## Data Protection

- Encrypt sensitive data at rest using `aes-256-gcm` with `ENCRYPTION_KEY` env var.
- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII).
- Sanitize error messages before returning to clients — log full details internally.

## Rate Limiting

Use `withRateLimit()` for public endpoints. Implement per-user rate limiting with `Retry-After` header on 429 responses.

## HTTPS

- All production traffic over HTTPS.
- WebSockets use `wss://` only.
- See `https-configuration.mdc` for local dev proxy setup.
